# Containerized Deployment Standards

Follow the canonical standard: **`.ai/standards/kamal-docker.md`**

Key rules:
- Multi-stage Docker builds; pin the Ruby base image; run as non-root
- Never bake secrets into images — inject at runtime; add a `HEALTHCHECK`
- Kamal: define web/worker roles and accessories; manage secrets via `.kamal/secrets`
- Use zero-downtime rollouts with health checks; tag images by git SHA
- Run DB migrations as a gated, idempotent release step
- No `latest` tags in production; every deploy plan includes rollback steps

